article.description: Andrea Riley scored 23 points and No. 19 Oklahoma State extended its non-conference home-winning streak to 26 with a 91-45 victory against Arkansas-Pine Bluff on Saturday.
article.headline: No. 19 Cowgirls extend non-conference home winning streak to 26
article.linkText: No. 19 Oklahoma State extends home win streak
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Andrea Riley scored 23 points and No. 19 Oklahoma State extended its non-conference home-winning streak to 26 with a 91-45 victory against Arkansas-Pine Bluff on Saturday.

Riley, who also had 10 assists, led five Cowgirls in double figures. Kristin Hernandez scored 15 points, and Megan Byford and Shaunte Smith had 14 apiece.

After struggling early, the Cowgirls (2-1) finished the first half on a 30-11 run to lead 42-20 at the break.

Arkansas-Pine Bluff (1-2) hit just 5-of-27 field-goal attempts in the opening 20 minutes and 13-of-61 for the game. Oklahoma State forced the Lady Lions into 27 turnovers.

Ciara Shields led Arkansas-Pine Bluff with 11 points and Tashalya Jackson had 10.
